(Republished)

In the Matter of Joseph Eisenberg, Respondent. William H. Ross, Appellant.

Motion for reargument granted, the prior decision of this court herein recalled and the order entered thereon on February 26, 1957, vacated and, upon reargument, the order appealed from is unanimously modified so as to fix the monthly rental at $129.37. Settle order on notice. Concur — Breitel, J. P., Rabin, Frank and Valente, JJ. [See ante, pp. 699, 819.]
